</div>

<!-- SETUP -->
<div id="setup" class="setup-section">
  <span class="section-label">Before You Start - Read Once</span>
  <div class="setup-grid">

    <div class="setup-block">
      <h3>iPhone 16 Pro Settings</h3>
      <div class="setting-row"><span class="setting-label">Resolution</span><span class="setting-value">4K at 30fps</span></div>
      <div class="setting-row"><span class="setting-label">Format</span><span class="setting-value">High Efficiency</span></div>
      <div class="setting-row"><span class="setting-label">Stabilization</span><span class="setting-value">Standard - ON</span></div>
      <div class="setting-row"><span class="setting-label">White Balance Lock</span><span class="setting-value">ON</span></div>
      <div class="setting-row"><span class="setting-label">Orientation</span><span class="setting-value">Portrait - always</span></div>
      <div class="setup-note">Inside the camera app - tap your face to lock focus and exposure. Hold until you see AE/AF LOCK at the top. Do this before every video.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="setup-block">
      <h3>Framing Rules</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Eyes land in the top third of the frame - not centered</li>
        <li>Small space above your head - about two fingers worth</li>
        <li>Shoulders and chest in frame - never cut at the neck</li>
        <li>Solo: sit or stand 3-4 feet from the phone</li>
        <li>Duo: both of you 4-5 feet back, side by side, equal space</li>
        <li>Phone at eye level or very slightly above - never below</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="setup-block">
      <h3>Audio</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>DJI Mic Mini clipped 6-8 inches below your chin</li>
        <li>Connect receiver to iPhone via USB-C before opening camera</li>
        <li>Do a 10-second test recording to confirm audio is coming through</li>
        <li>Close doors, turn off fans or AC - anything that hums</li>
        <li>Soft rooms sound better than bare hard walls</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="setup-block">
      <h3>Lighting</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Ring light directly in front, slightly above eye level</li>
        <li>If it feels harsh, back it up or move it slightly to the side</li>
        <li>No bright windows or light sources behind you</li>
        <li>Soft, even light on your face is the goal</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="setup-note">Try at least 2 different backdrops across the 9 videos. Keep it clean - no clutter, no logos, nothing that competes with you.</div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>


<!-- BUCKET 1 -->
<div id="bucket1">
  <div class="bucket-header">
    <div class="bucket-number">01</div>
    <div class="bucket-info">
      <h2>Business Exit Planning</h2>
      <p>Avatar: Mark &amp; Meredith &nbsp;·&nbsp; Pillar: Founder / Entrepreneur</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- VIDEO 1 -->
  <div class="video-card">
    <div class="card-header">
      <div>
        <div class="card-num">Video 01</div>
        <div class="card-title">Business Exit Planning</div>
      </div>
      <span class="format-badge badge-duo">Duo</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <div class="card-left">
        <span class="card-section-title">Gear for this shot</span>
        <ul class="gear-list">
          <li>Mic Mini on both of you</li>
          <li>Tripod - both in frame</li>
          <li>Ring light centered on you both</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="card-section-title">Before you hit record</span>
        <ul class="check-list">
          <li>Both mics connected and tested</li>
          <li>Both of you in frame, equal space</li>
          <li>Eyes in top third of frame</li>
          <li>Room is quiet</li>
          <li>Focus locked</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="runtime-tag">45-60 seconds</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-right">
        <span class="card-section-title">Script</span>
        <div class="script-block">
          <div class="script-speaker">Nichole</div>
          <div class="script-line">One of the biggest myths in business ownership is that when you're ready to leave, you just... leave. Most owners we sit down with have built something incredible - but they've also built themselves into every corner of it.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="script-block">
          <div class="script-speaker">Jalyn</div>
          <div class="script-line">And that's the part nobody talks about early enough. If the business can't run without you, it's not really sellable yet. That's not a criticism - it's just the reality most people find out too late.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="script-block">
          <div class="script-speaker">Nichole</div>
          <div class="script-line">Exit planning isn't something you do when you're ready to go. It's something you build toward - sometimes 5, 10 years out.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="disclaimer-block">
          <div class="script-speaker">Both - to close</div>
          <div class="script-line">This is just our opinion - reach out for personalized advice.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- VIDEO 2 -->
  <div class="video-card">
    <div class="card-header">
      <div>
        <div class="card-num">Video 02</div>
        <div class="card-title">Business Exit Planning</div>
      </div>
      <span class="format-badge badge-nichole">Nichole Solo</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <div class="card-left">
        <span class="card-section-title">Gear for this shot</span>
        <ul class="gear-list">
          <li>Mic Mini on Nichole</li>
          <li>Tripod - single frame</li>
          <li>Ring light on Nichole</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="card-section-title">Before you hit record</span>
        <ul class="check-list">
          <li>Mic connected and tested</li>
          <li>Single frame, clean backdrop</li>
          <li>Eyes in top third of frame</li>
          <li>Room is quiet</li>
          <li>Focus locked on face</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="runtime-tag">45-60 seconds</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-right">
        <span class="card-section-title">Script</span>
        <div class="script-block">
          <div class="script-speaker">Nichole</div>
          <div class="script-line">I've sat across from business owners who've spent 30 years building something they love - and when it's time to think about stepping back, they realize the business and their retirement are the same thing. No separation. No plan B.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="script-block">
          <div class="script-speaker">Nichole</div>
          <div class="script-line">The earlier you start thinking about what exit actually looks like, the more options you have. More time means more leverage - over the sale price, the terms, the timeline, and your own peace of mind.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="script-block">
          <div class="script-speaker">Nichole</div>
          <div class="script-line">If you're a business owner and you haven't had this conversation yet, that's exactly where we start.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="disclaimer-block">
          <div class="script-speaker">Nichole - to close</div>
          <div class="script-line">This is just our opinion - reach out for personalized advice.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- VIDEO 3 -->
  <div class="video-card">
    <div class="card-header">
      <div>
        <div class="card-num">Video 03</div>
        <div class="card-title">Business Exit Planning</div>
      </div>
      <span class="format-badge badge-jalyn">Jalyn Solo</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <div class="card-left">
        <span class="card-section-title">Gear for this shot</span>
        <ul class="gear-list">
          <li>Mic Mini on Jalyn</li>
          <li>Tripod - single frame</li>
          <li>Ring light on Jalyn</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="card-section-title">Before you hit record</span>
        <ul class="check-list">
          <li>Mic connected and tested</li>
          <li>Different backdrop from Video 02</li>
          <li>Eyes in top third of frame</li>
          <li>Room is quiet</li>
          <li>Focus locked on face</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="runtime-tag">30-45 seconds</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-right">
        <span class="card-section-title">Script</span>
        <div class="script-block">
          <div class="script-speaker">Jalyn</div>
          <div class="script-line">Something I think about a lot with business owner clients is identity. What happens to Mark when the business isn't there anymore?</div>
        </div>
        <div class="script-block">
          <div class="script-speaker">Jalyn</div>
          <div class="script-line">A lot of owners pour everything into what they've built. Their schedule, their relationships, their sense of purpose. And exit planning has to account for that too - not just the financial side.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="script-block">
          <div class="script-speaker">Jalyn</div>
          <div class="script-line">The goal is to build a life that's ready for what's next. Not just a business that's ready to sell.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="disclaimer-block">
          <div class="script-speaker">Jalyn - to close</div>
          <div class="script-line">This is just our opinion - reach out for personalized advice.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<!-- BUCKET 2 -->
<div id="bucket2">
  <div class="bucket-header">
    <div class="bucket-number">02</div>
    <div class="bucket-info">
      <h2>Habits of High Earners</h2>
      <p>Avatar: Jenny &amp; John &nbsp;·&nbsp; Pillar: Personal / Life in Balance</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- VIDEO 4 -->
  <div class="video-card">
    <div class="card-header">
      <div>
        <div class="card-num">Video 04</div>
        <div class="card-title">Habits of High Earners</div>
      </div>
      <span class="format-badge badge-duo">Duo</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <div class="card-left">
        <span class="card-section-title">Gear for this shot</span>
        <ul class="gear-list">
          <li>Mic Mini on both of you</li>
          <li>Tripod - both in frame</li>
          <li>Ring light centered on you both</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="card-section-title">Before you hit record</span>
        <ul class="check-list">
          <li>Both mics connected and tested</li>
          <li>Both of you in frame, equal space</li>
          <li>Eyes in top third of frame</li>
          <li>Room is quiet</li>
          <li>Focus locked</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="runtime-tag">45-60 seconds</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-right">
        <span class="card-section-title">Script</span>
        <div class="script-block">
          <div class="script-speaker">Nichole</div>
          <div class="script-line">Something I see consistently with high earners who actually build wealth over time - they pay themselves first. Before the bills, before the lifestyle spend, before everything else.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="script-block">
          <div class="script-speaker">Jalyn</div>
          <div class="script-line">And they're thinking about taxes - not just this year's bill, but what it looks like 10, 15 years from now. That's a completely different conversation than most people are having.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="script-block">
          <div class="script-speaker">Nichole</div>
          <div class="script-line">The income is there. The question is whether the habits around it are working as hard as you are.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="disclaimer-block">
          <div class="script-speaker">Both - to close</div>
          <div class="script-line">This is just our opinion - reach out for personalized advice.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- VIDEO 5 -->
  <div class="video-card">
    <div class="card-header">
      <div>
        <div class="card-num">Video 05</div>
        <div class="card-title">Habits of High Earners</div>
      </div>
      <span class="format-badge badge-nichole">Nichole Solo</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <div class="card-left">
        <span class="card-section-title">Gear for this shot</span>
        <ul class="gear-list">
          <li>Mic Mini on Nichole</li>
          <li>Tripod - single frame</li>
          <li>Ring light on Nichole</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="card-section-title">Before you hit record</span>
        <ul class="check-list">
          <li>Mic connected and tested</li>
          <li>Single frame, clean backdrop</li>
          <li>Eyes in top third of frame</li>
          <li>Room is quiet</li>
